  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-popper-pork-and-beef-smash-burger-with-fries/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways and deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon)</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> and cook for 1-2 min on each side or until lightly charred (reserve the pan!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-popper-pork-and-beef-smash-burger-with-fries/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>pork & beef mince</strong> in a bowl with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix until combined, then equally divide and shape into 2 meatballs per person</p><p>Cover the <strong>meatballs</strong> with a sheet of <strong>baking</strong> <strong>paper</strong> and roll them out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a rolling pin until evenly flattened – these are your <strong>patties</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-popper-pork-and-beef-smash-burger-with-fries/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop the <strong>charred chilli </strong>finely</p><p>Combine your <strong>chopped chilli </strong>and <strong>soft cheese </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> – this is your <strong>green chilli popper sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-popper-pork-and-beef-smash-burger-with-fries/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Combine your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a large bowl – this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>salad </strong>and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> to the bowl and give everything a gentle mix – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-popper-pork-and-beef-smash-burger-with-fries/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>patties</strong>, press them down very firmly with a spatula and cook for 3-4 min on each side, pressing down continuously, or until slightly charred and cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>smashed patties</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-popper-pork-and-beef-smash-burger-with-fries/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half (if required!)</p><p>Remove the tray[s] from the oven and place the<strong> brioche halves </strong>(cut side up!) on top of the fries</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 2-3 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-popper-pork-and-beef-smash-burger-with-fries/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To build the burger, top the <strong>warmed brioche base </strong>with the <strong>sliced tomato</strong>, a <strong>smashed patty</strong>, some of the <strong>green chilli popper sauce</strong>, the <strong>remaining smashed patty</strong>, the <strong>remaining green chilli popper sauce</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>sriracha</strong> and the <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>brioche</strong> <strong>lid</strong> – this is your <strong>green chilli popper smash burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>dressed salad </strong>and <strong>fries</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
